sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client
    participant TrustyAI as TrustyAI Service<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant ModelServer as Model Server<br/>(KServe/ModelMesh)<br/>gRPC
    participant Storage as Storage Backend<br/>(PVC CSV / MariaDB)
    participant Prometheus as Prometheus<br/>8080/TCP HTTP

    Note over Client,Prometheus: Flow 1: ModelMesh Inference Payload Ingestion
    participant ModelMesh as ModelMesh Serving
    ModelMesh->>TrustyAI: POST /consumer/kserve/v2<br/>8080/TCP HTTP, No Auth
    TrustyAI->>Storage: Store inference data<br/>File I/O (CSV) or JDBC (3306/TCP)

    Note over Client,Prometheus: Flow 2: KServe CloudEvent Payload Ingestion
    participant KServe as KServe InferenceLogger
    KServe->>TrustyAI: CloudEvent (request/response)<br/>8080/TCP HTTP, No Auth
    TrustyAI->>Storage: Store inference data<br/>File I/O (CSV) or JDBC (3306/TCP)

    Note over Client,Prometheus: Flow 3: On-Demand Explanation Generation
    Client->>TrustyAI: POST /explainers/local/lime<br/>8080/TCP HTTP, No Auth
    TrustyAI->>Storage: Load historical data
    Storage-->>TrustyAI: Inference dataset
    TrustyAI->>ModelServer: gRPC ModelInfer<br/>KServe V2 Protocol, No TLS
    ModelServer-->>TrustyAI: Inference results
    TrustyAI-->>Client: JSON explanation response

    Note over Client,Prometheus: Flow 4: Scheduled Metric Publishing
    Note right of TrustyAI: PrometheusScheduler (cron)<br/>triggers metric computation
    TrustyAI->>Storage: Read inference data
    Storage-->>TrustyAI: Dataset for metrics
    Note right of TrustyAI: Compute SPD, DIR,<br/>drift metrics
    Note right of TrustyAI: Publish to Micrometer<br/>Prometheus registry
    Prometheus->>TrustyAI: GET /q/metrics<br/>8080/TCP HTTP<br/>Auth: Bearer Token (SA)
    TrustyAI-->>Prometheus: Prometheus metrics
